What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Synthetic Vision System Market?

Market Analysis and Insights:

Global Synthetic Vision System Market

Synthetic vision system market is expected to reach USD 316.27 million by 2028 witnessing market growth at a rate of 4.0% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on synthetic vision system market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth.

A synthetic vision system (SVS) is a computer-mediated aerial vehicle reality system that uses 3D to provide pilots with simple and intuitive ways to perceive their flying environment. Synthetic vision provides operators with situational knowledge through the use of landscape, obstacle, geo-political, hydrological and other databases. A collection of databases stored on board the aircraft, an image generator computer, and a monitor are used for a standard SVS programme. Navigation solution is obtained through the use of GPS and inertial reference systems.

Increasing reliable operations at poor visibility, increasing requirement of enhanced aircraft safety in limited visibility environment such as in rain, fog, snow and haze, growing demand of aircrafts with advanced technological innovations, prevalence of smaller airports with inadequate infrastructure, increasing preferences of the consumer regarding safety and situational awareness are some of the major as well as vital factors which will likely to augment the growth of the synthetic vision system market in the projected timeframe of 2021-2028. On the other hand, increasing growth of the retrofit and aftermarkets along with increasing demand of standard fit for business jets and operational efficiency for aircraft which will further contribute by generating massive opportunities that will lead to the growth of the synthetic vision system market in the above mentioned projected timeframe.

Increasing cost of technology along with growing number of industry regulations which will likely to act as market restraints factor for the growth of the synthetic vision system in the above mentioned projected timeframe. Increasing need to create awareness among the aircraft operators which will become the biggest and foremost challenge for the growth of the market.

